## Knowledge Compounding Rule
Every skill invocation should leave the workspace smarter than before.

After generating any significant artifact:
- Add it to the appropriate `02-KNOWLEDGE/` subfolder
- Update `02-KNOWLEDGE/index.md`
- Note in `03-INITIATIVES/` if it affects an active initiative

This is what separates a workspace from a one-shot prompt.

---

## Document Quality Standards
- Every deliverable: title, date, author, status (Draft / Review / Final)
- Use TEMPLATES/ — never invent new formats
- User stories: "As a [persona], I want [action] so that [outcome]"
- Acceptance criteria: "Given [context], when [action], then [result]"
- All claims tagged: `[Assumed]` / `[Research-backed]` / `[Data-backed]`
- Decision docs: options considered, tradeoffs, recommendation, rationale

---

## TEMP Folder Protocol
When content is dropped into `TEMP/`:
- Identify the type (transcript / feedback / notes / research)
- Extract: decisions, action items, insights, open questions
- Identify which `01-COMPANY-CONTEXT/`, `02-KNOWLEDGE/`, or `03-INITIATIVES/` file to update
- Draft the update and confirm before writing
- Remind to clear TEMP after processing

---

## Token Efficiency
- MEMORY.md controls what to load — read it first, don't scan everything
- Read index.md files before scanning full folders
- In PRODUCT_SENSE mode, ask one powerful question at a time — don't barrage
- When generating long documents, produce section by section unless "full draft" is asked
